Privacy Policy
Effective Date:
12 March 2023
Last Updated:
9 December 2024
17V28 LTD ("we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and disclose your information when you use our mobile application (the "App") and services (collectively, the "Services"). By using our Services, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.
1. Information We Collect
1. Information We Collect
1.1 Personal Data
Currently, we do not collect personally identifiable information from our users. However, in the future, when registration and sign-in features are implemented, we may collect data such as:
Name
Email address
Phone number
Address, State, Province, ZIP/Postal code, City
Providing this information will be necessary to access certain features of the App, such as account creation or premium services. We will use this data to manage your account, provide customer support, and ensure compliance with our Terms of Use. This information may be shared with third-party service providers to facilitate these purposes, as detailed in Section 4 of this Privacy Policy.
1.2 Usage Data
We collect information that your device sends when you use our Services ("Usage Data"). This may include information such as your device's Internet Protocol (IP) address, device name, operating system version, the configuration of the App, the time and date of your use, and other statistics.
1.3 Cookies and Tracking Technologies
We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to track activity on our Services and hold certain information. These may include:
Session Cookies
: To operate our Services.
Analytics Cookies
: To understand and improve user behavior.
Third-Party Cookies
: To enable third-party features such as advertisements or analytics.
You can instruct your browser to refuse all cookies or to indicate when a cookie is being sent. Additionally, some cookie preferences may be managed within the app settings. However, if you do not accept cookies, you may not be able to use some portions of our Services.
2. Use of Data
We use the collected data for various purposes, including:
To provide and maintain our Services
To notify you about changes to our Services
To allow you to participate in interactive features of our Services
To provide customer support
To gather analysis or valuable information to improve our Services
To monitor the usage of our Services
To detect, prevent, and address technical issues
3. Disclosure of Data
We may disclose your Personal Data in the good faith belief that such action is necessary to:
Comply with a legal obligation
Protect and defend the rights or property of 17V28 LTD
Prevent or investigate possible wrongdoing in connection with the Services
Protect the personal safety of users of the Services or the public
Protect against legal liability
If your Personal Data is disclosed due to legal obligations or other reasons outlined above, we will make reasonable efforts to notify you where permitted by law. Notifications will be sent through the contact information provided in your account or via in-app alerts.
